courseSummaryDetails.courseDescription: Basic principles of mechanics and experiments in mechanics for physical science and engineering majors. Lecture tutorial and lab components must all be taken to receive credit. Maximum 5 credits allowed for any combination of <span class="linkified" data-id="cbf8dfdb-2210-4c79-8f19-d4316210ee69" data-subject="PHYS" data-number="114"  data-title="Mechanics" data-text="PHYS 114" />, <span class="linkified" data-id="f0ba3ec8-6bf5-4c04-8e7a-33cd00e8c36b" data-subject="PHYS" data-number="117"  data-title="General Physics Laboratory: Mechanics" data-text="PHYS 117" />, <span class="linkified" data-id="44b5ef70-1e64-431f-8e8e-24e4d0b94caf" data-subject="PHYS" data-number="121"  data-title="Mechanics" data-text="PHYS 121" />, and <span class="linkified" data-id="f47c7cfa-14ce-4867-a1b5-f57f193d782a" data-subject="PHYS" data-number="141"  data-title="Honors Mechanics" data-text="PHYS 141" />.
requisites: Either <span class="linkified" data-id="893bce1c-dd87-46e4-9830-6a10fc908e6f" data-subject="MATH" data-number="124"  data-title="Calculus with Analytic Geometry I" data-text="MATH 124" /> or <span class="linkified" data-id="13cb575b-da04-41a8-908d-a22166a8b829" data-subject="MATH" data-number="134"  data-title="Accelerated [Honors] Calculus" data-text="MATH 134" />, which may be taken concurrently.
